IT appears Home Affairs Minister Malusi Gigaba will not see the end of the “sex tape” scandal that shocked Mzansi over the weekend. In a series of tweets on Sunday morning, Gigaba said the tape was stolen during a phone hacking incident in 2016 or 2017, and that its content was only meant to be viewed by his wife and himself. As if the actual tape was not bad enough, now a song about it is making the rounds on the internet. A young DJ by the name of Enosse Makinta has decided to add to Gigaba’s misery, while hopefully making a name for himself, by making a Gqom track about the tape. The song is mostly instrumentals, with the minimal lyrics being the now famous words from Gigaba’s tape. It already has over a thousand views on YouTube. Listen to the song below:   